        <briefdescription>
<para>This function sends a command to wrap a given key using a specified AES wrapping key. </para>        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para><parameterlist kind="param"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>ClientParamsPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to the XAsu_ClientParams structure which holds the client input parameters. </para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
<parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>KeyWrapParamsPtr</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Pointer to <ref refid="struct_x_asu___key_wrap_params" kindref="compound">XAsu_KeyWrapParams</ref> structure which holds the parameters of key wrap input arguments.</para></parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
<simplesect kind="return"><para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>XST_SUCCESS, if IPI request to ASU is sent successfully.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XASU_INVALID_ARGUMENT, if any argument is invalid.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XASU_INVALID_UNIQUE_ID, if received Queue ID is invalid.</para></listitem><listitem><para>XST_FAILURE, if sending an IPI request to ASU fails. </para></listitem></itemizedlist>
</para></simplesect>
</para>        </detaileddescription>
